      <p class="step-label">Step 6 of 9</p>
      <h1>Set Up a Workspace</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Choose a place where the team can meet, store supplies, and actually work on the robot.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <p>A workspace can be a classroom, maker space, library room, garage, or another safe area where the team can build and test.</p>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Workspace checklist</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Room for a table, tools, and storage bins</li>
            <li>Access to power and good lighting</li>
            <li>A place for computers and notebooks</li>
            <li>Clear rules for safety and cleanup</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Decide where the team will meet consistently and what equipment can stay there.</p>
      </section>
